1532
01:30:13.166 --> 01:30:16.726
So ovarian cancer is the most lethal gynecological malignancy

1533
01:30:16.766 --> 01:30:20.446
worldwide. And among its subtypes, epithelial ovarian cancer

1534
01:30:21.026 --> 01:30:24.166
is the most common and most aggressive one.

1535
01:30:26.546 --> 01:30:30.326
Most of the ovarian cancer patients get diagnosed at a very late stage

1536
01:30:30.846 --> 01:30:34.726
and when the disease has already progressed and therapeutic

1537
01:30:36.086 --> 01:30:39.266
options have become limited. But that is not the only

1538
01:30:39.726 --> 01:30:41.026
problem in ovarian cancer.

1539
01:30:41.946 --> 01:30:45.846
In ovarian cancer, most of the patients initially respond to

1540
01:30:45.886 --> 01:30:46.926
existing therapies.

1541
01:30:47.996 --> 01:30:51.366
But more than 70% of the patients ultimately relapse,

1542
01:30:51.746 --> 01:30:55.406
and the recurrent disease is harder to treat because of drug

1543
01:30:55.426 --> 01:30:56.046
resistance.

1544
01:30:57.546 --> 01:31:00.386
For example, the development of PARP inhibitors.

1545
01:31:01.286 --> 01:31:05.126
PARP inhibitors have significantly improved ovarian cancer management,

1546
01:31:05.606 --> 01:31:09.086
but tumors ultimately get resistant to these drugs as well.

1547
01:31:10.206 --> 01:31:13.646
More importantly, resistance doesn't arise from a single mechanism.

1548
01:31:14.546 --> 01:31:18.266
Tumor cells adapt by-Activating multiple DNA

1549
01:31:18.306 --> 01:31:21.886
repair or survival pathways. So we need new

1550
01:31:21.926 --> 01:31:25.446
therapies which can target these multiple resistance mechanisms

1551
01:31:25.566 --> 01:31:26.506
simultaneously.

1552
01:31:27.886 --> 01:31:29.706
This is where microRNAs become interesting.

1553
01:31:30.506 --> 01:31:34.086
MicroRNAs are small non-coding RNAs that

1554
01:31:34.646 --> 01:31:38.266
specifically bind to the three prime untranslated region of their

1555
01:31:38.306 --> 01:31:40.916
target mRNAs by partial complementarity.

1556
01:31:41.826 --> 01:31:45.366
So because the microRNAs don't need perfect complementarity, a single

1557
01:31:45.446 --> 01:31:49.366
microRNA can target multiple transcripts, and this allows

1558
01:31:49.406 --> 01:31:52.786
microRNA to target resistance as a mechanism,

1559
01:31:52.926 --> 01:31:56.726
as a network, not just as a single

1560
01:31:56.786 --> 01:31:57.466
target agent.

1561
01:31:59.116 --> 01:32:02.346
So in cancer, there can be two different types of microRNAs.

1562
01:32:03.086 --> 01:32:06.906
One is oncogenic microRNAs, which gets upregulated and promotes cancer

1563
01:32:06.966 --> 01:32:10.726
progression. And by suppressing their

1564
01:32:10.766 --> 01:32:13.446
activity, we can have therapeutic benefits.

1565
01:32:14.046 --> 01:32:17.766
But we are mostly focusing on tumor-suppressive microRNAs, which gets

1566
01:32:17.826 --> 01:32:21.726
downregulated in cancer cells, and by increasing their expression in the

1567
01:32:21.786 --> 01:32:24.426
cancer cells, we can inhibit tumor cell growth.

1568
01:32:24.966 --> 01:32:28.546
And for this, our lab mostly focuses on using microRNA mimics.

1569
01:32:30.206 --> 01:32:31.926
But why we chose microRNA-15a?

1570
01:32:33.626 --> 01:32:37.566
MicroRNA-15a is a known tumor-suppressive microRNA which

1571
01:32:37.586 --> 01:32:41.526
gets downregulated in multiple cancer types, including epithelial ovarian

1572
01:32:41.586 --> 01:32:42.556
cancer. And

1573
01:32:44.186 --> 01:32:47.906
some of the targets of microRNA-15a, like BCL2, E1, CHEK1,

1574
01:32:48.006 --> 01:32:51.886
BMI1, and YAP1, they all are involved in pathways which

1575
01:32:51.926 --> 01:32:53.666
drive ovarian cancer progression.

1576
01:32:54.906 --> 01:32:57.576
So by restoring microRNA-15a level, we can

1577
01:32:57.866 --> 01:33:01.086
reduce the expression of these proteins, and

1578
01:33:01.126 --> 01:33:02.926
thereby can inhibit

1579
01:33:03.826 --> 01:33:05.646
the tube ovarian cancer progression.

1580
01:33:06.766 --> 01:33:10.626
One more interesting fact is that the ATR CHEK1/E1 axis is

1581
01:33:10.646 --> 01:33:14.626
heavily involved, plays a crucial role in development of resistance

1582
01:33:14.646 --> 01:33:17.846
towards PARP inhibitors. So as we saw that

1583
01:33:17.866 --> 01:33:21.566
microRNA-15a targets both E1 and CHEK1, it has the

1584
01:33:21.586 --> 01:33:25.106
potential to resensitize the ovarian cancer cells, which has become

1585
01:33:25.125 --> 01:33:27.526
resistant towards PARP inhibitors.

1586
01:33:28.546 --> 01:33:31.206
Now, to increase the therapeutic potency,

1587
01:33:33.446 --> 01:33:37.106
stability, and delivery, we have modified this

1588
01:33:37.146 --> 01:33:38.426
microRNA with

1589
01:33:39.546 --> 01:33:43.166
two nucleoside analogs, uracil and 5-FU and gemcitabine.

1590
01:33:43.566 --> 01:33:47.466
So we have replaced all the uracil and cytidine molecules in the guide

1591
01:33:47.586 --> 01:33:50.486
strand using 5-FU and gemcitabine.

1592
01:33:50.846 --> 01:33:54.236
And 5-FU and gemcitabine are known chemotherapeutic drugs that

1593
01:33:54.346 --> 01:33:57.246
causes DNA damage and replication stress.

1594
01:33:58.646 --> 01:34:02.106
On the other hand, we conjugated methotrexate to the passenger strand.

1595
01:34:02.826 --> 01:34:06.606
Methotrexate is a folate analog, so it can go and specifically

1596
01:34:06.666 --> 01:34:10.566
bind to the overexpressed folate receptors in ovarian cancer

1597
01:34:10.646 --> 01:34:14.046
cells, and thereby increasing the tumor targeting specificity.

1598
01:34:14.866 --> 01:34:18.406
So with this modified microRNA mimic, we wanted to combine the

1599
01:34:18.426 --> 01:34:21.826
tumor-suppressive functions of microRNA-15a

1600
01:34:21.906 --> 01:34:25.726
with chemotherapeutic drugs. And we expected

1601
01:34:25.806 --> 01:34:26.006
that

1602
01:34:27.446 --> 01:34:30.646
this will increase the therapeutic potential of this modified microRNA.

1603
01:34:32.686 --> 01:34:36.146
So first, we wanted to test its efficacy

1604
01:34:36.166 --> 01:34:39.846
across a panel of ovarian cancer cells with

1605
01:34:40.066 --> 01:34:43.686
diverse BRCA and P53 status. And we saw that the

1606
01:34:43.706 --> 01:34:47.626
modified microRNA significantly reduced ovarian cancer cell viability

1607
01:34:48.406 --> 01:34:52.106
and at a very low dose of at nanomolar concentration.

1608
01:34:52.726 --> 01:34:56.106
And most importantly, without using any delivery vehicle, which is a major

1609
01:34:56.146 --> 01:34:58.436
challenge in nucleic acid-based therapies.

1610
01:34:59.846 --> 01:35:03.586
Also, it was several thousandfold more potent than standard

1611
01:35:03.686 --> 01:35:04.966
PARP inhibitor olaparib.

1612
01:35:06.086 --> 01:35:09.706
We also saw that the modified microRNA increased apoptosis in

1613
01:35:09.766 --> 01:35:13.566
these ovarian cancer cells and caused cell cycle disruption

1614
01:35:13.666 --> 01:35:16.806
and as shown by reduction in G2/S ratio.

1615
01:35:17.706 --> 01:35:21.506
So this data together suggests that the modified microRNA shows low

1616
01:35:21.586 --> 01:35:25.266
nanomolar potency across ovarian cancer models with diverse

1617
01:35:25.286 --> 01:35:28.926
genetic backgrounds, like irrespective of their BRCA or

1618
01:35:28.946 --> 01:35:29.966
P53 status.

1619
01:35:31.226 --> 01:35:34.856
But that was only the part of the story. We wanted to overcome drug resistance.

1620
01:35:35.566 --> 01:35:39.506
So for this, we generated olaparib-resistant ovarian cancer cells, as

1621
01:35:39.566 --> 01:35:42.166
shown by increased olaparib IC50 values.

1622
01:35:42.866 --> 01:35:46.306
And we saw that the modified microRNA showed similar low nanomolar

1623
01:35:46.366 --> 01:35:49.966
potency in these drug-resistant cells as well.

1624
01:35:50.486 --> 01:35:54.306
It also increased apoptotic cell population and caused cell cycle

1625
01:35:54.346 --> 01:35:56.706
arrest, as we also saw in parental cells.

1626
01:35:58.406 --> 01:36:02.166
So this data suggests that the modified microRNA retained its low nanomolar

1627
01:36:02.246 --> 01:36:06.186
potency even when the ovarian cancer cells

1628
01:36:06.206 --> 01:36:08.246
became resistant towards olaparib.

1629
01:36:10.966 --> 01:36:11.106
So

1630
01:36:11.946 --> 01:36:15.826
next, we wanted to get more mechanistic insights, like how the modified microRNA

1631
01:36:15.866 --> 01:36:19.526
works. And for that, we did a whole RNA sequencing and

1632
01:36:19.786 --> 01:36:21.186
some KEGG pathway analysis.

1633
01:36:22.006 --> 01:36:25.906
And consistent with our design, we saw some upregulation of DNA

1634
01:36:25.966 --> 01:36:29.146
damage related pathways and apoptosis and necroptosis.

1635
01:36:29.806 --> 01:36:33.696
Interestingly, we also saw that some of the survival pathways like WNT,

1636
01:36:33.906 --> 01:36:37.106
