1637
01:36:38.626 --> 01:36:39.706
So this gives a

1638
01:36:40.946 --> 01:36:41.786
overall broad

1639
01:36:43.166 --> 01:36:46.966
view how our modified microRNA works, but we also wanted to get

1640
01:36:47.066 --> 01:36:50.986
more detailed insights. So for this, we did some heat

1641
01:36:51.026 --> 01:36:54.965
map analysis and western blot, and we saw that after modified microRNA

1642
01:36:54.986 --> 01:36:58.446
treatment, the DNA damage repair related genes and

1643
01:36:58.926 --> 01:37:00.966
P53 pathway genes get upregulated.

1644
01:37:01.576 --> 01:37:05.346
And some key checkpoint proteins like E1 and CHEK1, which we discussed

1645
01:37:05.446 --> 01:37:08.526
earlier, gets downregulated in both parental and resistant

1646
01:37:08.536 --> 01:37:09.766
cells.

1647
01:37:10.806 --> 01:37:11.886
At the same time, we saw

1648
01:37:12.706 --> 01:37:16.386
activation of genes like

1649
01:37:16.446 --> 01:37:20.106
CDK1 and CDC25A, which drives cells

1650
01:37:20.146 --> 01:37:23.970
towards mitosis.So to summarize all these findings, we

1651
01:37:24.010 --> 01:37:27.790
can say that the modified microRNA treatment increases DNA

1652
01:37:27.850 --> 01:37:29.170
damage and replication stress,

1653
01:37:30.010 --> 01:37:33.650
which activates p53 pathway. But at the same time, it

1654
01:37:33.690 --> 01:37:37.550
reduces the cell's ability to repair the damaged DNA by removing the

1655
01:37:37.810 --> 01:37:38.900
cell cycle checkpoints,

1656
01:37:40.170 --> 01:37:43.090
and thereby forcing the cells towards mitosis

1657
01:37:43.890 --> 01:37:46.950
with damaged DNA and leading to mitotic collapse.

1658
01:37:50.170 --> 01:37:54.110
So we took another step, and we wanted to check if the modified microRNA

1659
01:37:54.150 --> 01:37:56.430
can be used in combination with other drugs.

1660
01:37:57.090 --> 01:38:01.010
So for this, we did a Bliss synergy analysis, and we found that

1661
01:38:01.390 --> 01:38:04.170
the modified microRNA shows strong synergistic effect

1662
01:38:05.350 --> 01:38:05.870
with

1663
01:38:06.690 --> 01:38:08.310
olaparib, which is a PARP inhibitor.

1664
01:38:08.870 --> 01:38:12.370
So this shows that apart from using it as a

1665
01:38:12.450 --> 01:38:15.850
standalone therapy, we can also use it as a rational

1666
01:38:15.890 --> 01:38:17.270
combination partner

1667
01:38:18.130 --> 01:38:20.110
with existing therapies like olaparib.

1668
01:38:21.570 --> 01:38:25.310
So with this strong in vitro work, we also wanted to see if the similar

1669
01:38:25.750 --> 01:38:28.710
efficacy can be achieved in vivo settings as well.

1670
01:38:29.390 --> 01:38:33.370
So for this, we generated metastatic tumor model in mice using

1671
01:38:33.430 --> 01:38:34.350
both parental and

1672
01:38:37.830 --> 01:38:39.850
olaparib-resistant SCOP3 cells.

1673
01:38:39.890 --> 01:38:42.810
And we saw that in both cases, the modified microRNA treatment

1674
01:38:43.290 --> 01:38:45.950
significantly inhibited metastatic tumor growth.

1675
01:38:47.490 --> 01:38:51.270
And most importantly, at a very low dose of only 3.75

1676
01:38:51.330 --> 01:38:52.130
mg per kg.

1677
01:38:53.350 --> 01:38:57.070
And because we used such a low dose, we didn't see any

1678
01:38:57.150 --> 01:39:00.670
